  "texts": [
    "The equality of top-left and top-right parts of the figure can be taken as the definition of the 2-group symmetry being studied here.",
    "2.2A class [σ] of × valued 2-cochains on H L, such that any 2-cochain σ in the class [σ] satisfies the equation (167), and two 2-cochains σ, σ ′ ∈ [σ] are related by χ L [Θ] H L = 0 ∈ H 3 (H L, U(1)).",
    "The fusion of topological junction local operators generating the induced H L 0-form symmetry on L produces extra × factors captured by a 2-cochain σ on H L satisfyingχ L (Θ H L) = δσ.",
    "(175)Rescalings of these local operators induces an equivalence relationσ ∼ σ + δβ, (176)where β is a × valued 1-cochain on H L. Thus only the class [σ] of 2-cochains upto the above equivalence relation differentiates different 1-charges.",
    "2.2The simple 1-morphisms of C (q+1) G (0) are all endomorphisms of this single object and correspond to loops based at the marked point in BG (0).3."
